<TEXT>Your browser is unsupported We recommend using the latest version of IE11, Edge, Chrome, Firefox or Safari. University of Illinois Chicago Search the site University of Illinois Chicago Undergraduate Research Main Menu Expand About menu Expand Opportunities menu Eyebrow menu Undergraduate Affairs and Academic Programs Ask UIC UIC menu UIC.edu Campus Map Search Undergraduates who engage in supervised research, scholarship, and creative endeavors experience positive personal, academic, and professional benefits beyond those provided by other college experiences. Our staff offers UIC students from all backgrounds and in all majors information and resources that help them find, secure, and succeed in such experiences–on and off campus and nationally and internationally. We also support faculty and staff in mentoring students and garnering funding for their projects. We are home to a number of signature initiatives, including the Undergraduate Research Experience Chancellor’s Undergraduate Research Award , and a partner with campus units on several others. Advising: Students who would like to consult with or receive advising from the Office of Undergraduate Research and External Fellowships are encouraged to contact us by phone at (312) 355-2477 , by email at our@uic.edu , or to attend “no appointment necessary” office drop-in hours, located in 802 University Hall: Tuesdays 10:30am-12:30pm Wednesdays 10:30am-12:30pm Virtual Drop-in Hours: Students who would like to meet on-line can use this link to meet with office staff: https://uic.zoom.us/j/89548524487?pwd=bGpOQUhCU0RVejJkakE4RnZTUjZ3dz09 Thursdays 4:00pm-6:00pm Heading link xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link Heading link xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link Undergraduate Research Forum Heading link xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link Follow us Follow us University of Illinois Chicago Quick Links Undergraduate Research Experience Datab